        "short_description": "A pristine tropical rainforest famous for its untouched ecosystem and rare species like the Lion-tailed Macaque.",
        "detailed": "Silent Valley National Park, part of the Nilgiri Biosphere Reserve, is one of the last undisturbed rainforests in India. First botanically noted in 1847, its global fame grew in the 1970s when a major environmental movement stopped a proposed hydroelectric dam. In 1984, it was officially declared a National Park. The valley, known locally as Sairandhri, hosts unique flora and fauna."
